Laura Munro

About me

User experience Designer with a specialisation in user interface design and front-end development. I have several years of experience in the creative industry, working with startups, agencies and in government. My skills include UI design and development, creating and implementing design systems, designing for accessibility, and responsive design.

I have a keen eye for detail and enjoy working closely with developers through the delivery phase of projects. When I'm not designing I enjoy spending time with friends and family, working on creative projects and sewing, and drinking coffee. Currently a UX/UI Designer at ACC.

MyACC

The self service product for injuried New Zealanders to access support with ACC.

As the UX/UI Designer I am responsible for the discovery and design of new features, and provide on-going support for the development phase.
